OpenLMI Provider for Condor
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Condor is a workload management system for compute-intensive jobs. 
It's an open source HPC/HTC scheduler from e University of Wisconsin-Madison.
This is the core scheduler from Red Hat Enterprise MRG.

This provider will be based on the implementaion of SBLIM/IBM project of 
OpenPBS, the OpenPBS CIM Model. OpenPBS is based on PBS propietary software. 
The original Open Source version released in 1998, and is not actively 
developed.

Links:

The SBLIM CIM provider for OpenPBS:
http://sourceforge.net/apps/mediawiki/sblim/index.php?title=ProviderNcsaCoop
http://sblim.sourceforge.net/ncsa.html
http://sblim.sourceforge.net/instrumentation.html

The Condor project:
http://research.cs.wisc.edu/condor/

The OpenPBS project:
http://www.mcs.anl.gov/research/projects/openpbs/


Roadmap
~~~~~~~

The first prototype is developed in Python and SOAP Condor API for RAD.


J2EE -> Python CIM provider -> API SOAP -> Condor

